  "prompt": "How can corruption in India be erased?",
  "response": "Addressing corruption in India is complex and requires a multi-pronged approach:\n\n1. Stronger Legal Framework\n- Stricter anti-corruption laws\n- Faster prosecution of corrupt officials\n- Robust enforcement mechanisms\n\n2. Transparency\n- Digital governance\n- E-governance initiatives\n- Right to Information (RTI) Act implementation\n\n3. Systemic Reforms\n- Simplifying bureaucratic procedures\n- Reducing discretionary powers\n- Merit-based promotions\n\n4. Technology Integration\n- Digital payment systems\n- Online service delivery\n- Blockchain for transparent transactions\n\n5. Public Awareness\n- Education about corruption risks\n- Encouraging citizen reporting\n- Social movements against corruption\n\n6. Economic Reforms\n- Reducing complex regulations\n- Simplifying tax structures\n- Promoting ease of doing business\n\n7. Judicial Reforms\n- Speedy trial mechanisms\n- Independent and efficient judicial system\n- Accountability of judges\n\n8. Political Will\n- Strong political leadership\n- Zero tolerance for corruption\n- Exemplary punishments\n\n9. Ethical Education\n- Promoting integrity in schools\n- Value-based education\n- Developing civic responsibility\n\n10. Whistleblower Protection\n- Strong legal protections\n- Encouraging reporting of corrupt practices\n\nSustainable change requires consistent effort from government, institutions, and citizens.",
